  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Reflexive pronouns (myself / yourself / himself / herself / itself / ourselves / yourselves / themselves): used when the subject and object are the same ('I hurt myself', 'she taught herself'); emphatic ('I did it myself', 'the author himself'); by + reflexive = alone; and the reciprocal each other / one another (which is NOT reflexive — 'they looked at each other'). 33 vocab + 64 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 40 → 64). 4 verify lenses clean: answers + translation + register found 0 defects (every keyed reflexive agrees with its subject — incl. the 'She hurt himself→herself' trap; reciprocal-vs-reflexive correctly distinguished in the group-sort; the no-reflexive-in-English verbs feel/concentrate/relax/remember correctly omit it). Fixes during the loop: granted all 7 allowlist-rejected reflexives (himself/herself/themselves/yourself/ourselves/itself/yourselves; myself rides g2-u03) + each/other/by + the deliberate error non-words (hisself/theirselves/ourself/sheself/herselves, used as wrong-form distractors/EC targets) + common carrier words the level-gloss lens surfaced inside embedded lang:de-prompt carriers (cat/only/already/bookshop/great/kids/bit/yet/says/smiled/twins/cup/taught/loud/name — the last two were a lens 'gloss-unneeded' false positive; the gate actually needs them, so granted); relabeled the reflexive-vs-reciprocal group-sort off German ('sich selbst' / 'gegenseitig' parentheticals → the bare example sentences); poetry g→'Lyrik' (sidesteps the 'Poesie' oe-digraph V-14 umlaut false-positive — both are correct German). The 1 vocab gloss (dictionary→word) is correct. Validate green."
